The paper focuses on visually-aware recommender systems and proposes a novel approach to personalized clothing recommendation that models users' visual preferences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant areas for visual recommendation systems. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the use of interactive recommendation algorithms and visualizations, which suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
